        %h4 Figuring out flow and information architecture
        %p
          Due to the large scope of the product across web and mobile platforms, I looked at the large picture on what type of experience to provide, and how we would get there. In considering this large scope, we were able to break up the product into these core components:
        %ul.col-2
          .column
            %li Landing/Onboarding
            %li Authentication
            %li Notification
            %li Feed
          .column
            %li Communities
            %li User
            %li Settings
        %p
          Since we operated mobile-first, I figured out the flow and information architecture of the native iOS appliciation, taking into consideration native components based on the <a href="https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/userexperience/conceptual/mobilehig/" target="_blank">iOS Human Interface Guidelines</a>. While broad conceptual architecture across iOS and the web remained the same, their respective platforms allowed for diverging presentations of information.
        %figure.image-wrapper
          = image_tag("standin.jpg")
          %figcaption
            A preliminary sketch of Neon's information architecture of
            navigation, defined during the design sprint.

  .box
    %article.main-column.no-left
