          API was served through Rails, Backbone.js was used to create a
          performant front-end experience for the user. I collaborated closely
          with the Nixle developer, and we problem-solved often to ensure we
          were creating the cleanest and most easily maintainable code base. I
          wrote in HTML, SCSS, and Javascript, occasionally creating templates
          and views in Backbone.js.
